The paper deals with wireless sensor networks and estimation problems, which are typically studied in the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The paper also involves collaboration and coordination among the sensors, which falls under the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. The use of regular structures and geometric graphs suggests a possible connection to the Mathematics (cs.MA) sub-category. Finally, the paper presents analytical and simulation results, which are typical of the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
